<section class="px-6 py-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-4">How it works</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    Markdown files with YAML frontmatter in git are the source of truth. Pyrite
    builds a fast search index on top and exposes everything through multiple
    interfaces.
  </p>

  <img
    src="/diagram1.jpg"
    alt="Architecture diagram: git-versioned markdown files flow into a SQLite index (FTS5 + vector embeddings), which serves MCP Server, CLI, REST API, and Web UI. Any AI connects here."
    class="w-full rounded-xl"
    loading="lazy"
  />

  <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mt-10 text-sm">
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="text-pyrite-400 font-semibold mb-1">Source of truth</div>
      <div class="text-text-secondary">
        Plain markdown files in a git repo. Read them in any editor. Diff, branch,
        review.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="text-pyrite-400 font-semibold mb-1">Derived index</div>
      <div class="text-text-secondary">
        SQLite FTS5 + optional vector embeddings. Rebuild from files any time with
        <code class="text-text-primary">pyrite index build</code>.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="text-pyrite-400 font-semibold mb-1">Multiple interfaces</div>
      <div class="text-text-secondary">
        CLI for automation, MCP for AI agents, REST API for apps, Web UI for
        humans.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
